係推遲算 <br />\n歐洲爆到咁 隨時六七月仲爆得勁啲<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/please.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7b8ded61d5246d39a3adc5f81ee3706c983f6b14","tid":1920983,"uid":197098,"like":1,"dislike":12,"score":-11,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T05:34:12.000Z","msg":"I've been on holiday in many countries. I'd always thought that many other countries were better than Hong Kong but after I went to these countries on vacation, I realised that in terms of city life, nightlife, shopping and food, Hong Kong really is the best. In Europe, shops close at four on weekdays and don't open all at weekends except for big cities like London where shops close at six on weekdays and four at weekends. Their main sorts of entertainment are pubs and clubs. Las Vegas has spectacular night views but it was built primarily for tourism. It's famous for gambling, unique hotel design and shows like boxing events. However in terms of scenery, Scandinavia and Tibet are the most ravishing I would say. Tibet is famous for its breathtaking scenery at high altitude. Xinjiang is also a place of outstanding scenic beauty. If you think you might have altitude sickness such as headaches, dizziness or trouble sleeping, I suggest that you should bring some medicine along with you. In fact, my friend Susan who's just been to the Mount Everest base camp showed me her photos taken there by which I was awestruck. It's definitely a glamorous holiday destination. A tour of the base camp would be a once in a lifetime experience. Tibet is also the best place for stargazing in my opinion since it's much closer to the heaven than any other places on earth. It has some of the highest lakes in the world that are rich with fish and other marine life and the countryside is inhabited by flocks of yellow ducks as well as wild horses and donkeys. The lakes in Tibet such as Lake Paiku which is four thousand five hundred meters above sea level, reflect the beauty of the stars, giving a double view of the sky at night. You can even pitch a tent and camp there to get the best view of the stars and the Milky Way galaxy."},{"pid":"39ad9a0624cd091f870c2103db13abbc1c24bec3","tid":1920983,"uid":80671,"like":0,"dislike":10,"score":-10,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T05:38:27.000Z","msg":"六月想飛日本<br />\n趁$88買左UO機票，又book定堆可以free cancel 嘅酒店先，做好兩手準備"},{"pid":"859ba15965bed39f38a94a94624cedbb6bcfc6cf","tid":1920983,"uid":138402,"like":0,"dislike":5,"score":-5,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T05:42:33.000Z","msg":"7月中去澳洲exchange  好驚去唔到<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"6d2db161986a9122e8bc4646cccbffbd73410f6e","tid":1920983,"uid":140878,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T07:14:54.000Z","msg":"六月泰國<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n睇黎要cancel了"},{"pid":"c0131229f2d0c8d2bf7b0dfc39d8f37abc660c31","tid":1920983,"uid":35746,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T07:30:43.000Z","msg":"上個都會諗下，依家冇年尾都唔諗了"},{"pid":"af049d8684dcdae2dbd050d8d89f4734979a56a4","tid":1920983,"uid":229780,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T10:14:49.000Z","msg":"6月去睇歐國盃<br />\n真係凍過水<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1822a4db12cde39097213cd08e53c00392defafd","tid":1920983,"uid":35780,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"39ad9a0624cd091f870c2103db13abbc1c24bec3","tid":1920983,"uid":80671,"like":0,"dislike":10,"score":-10,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T05:38:27.000Z","msg":"六月想飛日本<br />\n趁$88買左UO機票，又book定堆可以free cancel 嘅酒店先，做好兩手準備"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-13T10:32:45.000Z","msg":"邊有咁多人同你爭酒店"},{"pid":"71b286467436a133dca78e16c02a06d837a4cd41","tid":1920983,"uid":156092,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-14T07:18:19.000Z","msg":"去條撚咩"},{"pid":"86